  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Broker Operator (Tanker)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Shipping Operations</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee daily operational activities, including coordination with terminals and counterparties for pre-fixture clearance.</li><li>Prepare and issue voyage instructions as well as loading and discharging guidelines.</li><li>Monitor vessel positions, track performance, and update systems to ensure accurate P&L reporting.</li><li>Maintain communication with masters, agents, and terminal representatives.</li><li>Supervise cargo operations, ensuring adherence to schedules and operational requirements.</li><li>Address and resolve day-to-day operational queries.</li><li>Manage bunkering activities, including arranging fuel supplies, monitoring consumption, and keeping track of market bunker prices.</li></ul><p><strong>Invoicing</strong></p><ul><li>Generate invoices for freight, shipping costs, and re-charge items.</li><li>Review and verify incoming invoices, including freight, AWRP, and other operational costs.</li><li>Process payable invoices related to service providers such as hire, port charges, and bunkering.</li></ul><p><strong>Demurrage / Claims</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare, calculate, negotiate, and finalize demurrage and related claims.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of hands-on experience in shipping operations, with specialization in clean tanker management.</li><li>Solid background in shipping operations with knowledge of regional trade routes, vessels, ports, and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Strong communication and teamwork skills.</li><li>Prior experience using Veson systems will be an advantage.</li><li>Proficiency in spoken communication is essential.</li></ul>",
